# Backend Rules

## Technology Stack

- NestJS
- TypeScript
- In-memory mock data (NO database)

## Structure

```
apps/server/src/
├── controllers/    # Thin HTTP layer
├── services/       # Business logic
├── data/           # Mock data
├── app.module.ts
└── main.ts
```

## Controller Rules

Controllers must be THIN:

```typescript
// ✅ CORRECT
@Controller('groups')
export class GroupsController {
  constructor(private readonly groupsService: GroupsService) {}

  @Get()
  findAll(): ApiResponse<Group[]> {
    const groups = this.groupsService.findAll();
    return { success: true, data: groups };
  }
}

// ❌ WRONG - Business logic in controller
@Controller('groups')
export class GroupsController {
  @Get()
  findAll(): ApiResponse<Group[]> {
    const groups = mockData.filter(g => g.active);
    return { success: true, data: groups };
  }
}
```

## Service Rules

Business logic lives in services:

```typescript
@Injectable()
export class GroupsService {
  findAll(): Group[] {
    return groups;
  }

  create(dto: CreateGroupDto, createdBy: string): Group {
    const newGroup: Group = {
      id: generateId(),
      ...dto,
      createdBy,
      createdAt: new Date(),
      updatedAt: new Date(),
    };
    groups.push(newGroup);
    return newGroup;
  }
}
```

## Response Format

ALL responses must use ApiResponse:

```typescript
interface ApiResponse<T> {
  success: boolean;
  data?: T;
  error?: string;
  message?: string;
}
```

## Mock Data

- Use in-memory arrays
- Simulate relational structure
- NO persistence
- Ready for future database migration
